# Deferred Editor Shell (Cursor Rule)

- The visible `MK_editor` shell is deferred after SDL3 removal; do not recreate the removed SDL3/Dear ImGui shell files without a focused native Win32/D3D12 plan.
- Keep `MK_editor_core` GUI-independent and covered by the default validation lane.
- `tools/build-gui.ps1`, `tools/evaluate-cpp23.ps1 -Gui`, and `MK_ENABLE_DESKTOP_GUI=ON` should fail closed until a first-party visible shell lands.
- Future shell caches and native handles must stay behind explicit private adapter APIs; do not add public mutable cache fields without an architecture decision.
- Editor-local `compile_flags.txt` fallbacks were removed with the old shell. Future shell work must add IDE fallback flags explicitly when needed. Full checklist: [`docs/agent-operational-reference.md`](../../docs/agent-operational-reference.md).
